Narrator

My next scheduled meeting was about the law enforcement budget with Nia and Lileas. I heard some knocks on the door.

Player

“That's a couple of minutes less of Lileas. Great.”

Nia Morgna

“This might come off as a little strange, but I am proud of you.”

Player

“Words are just words. Actions are what's important.”

Nia Morgna

“I can imagine. So much responsibility and so much power at the same time.”

Nia Morgna

“Everyone wants to be a president until they are one I guess.”

Player

“Nonsense. Our government is not a corrupt government.”

Player

“So finally you come to the point. What do you really want?”

Player

“Give me time to think about it.”

Nia Morgna

“I'm still figuring out the details myself right now, but think about the possibilities.”

Nia Morgna

“A chat about your emergency decree.”

Player

“Mistakes of Soll? He made this great country what it currently is.”

Nia Morgna

“No, not at all. We were just discussing...a few things.”

Lileas Graf

“Well then... Let's go straight in.”

Narrator

Lileas took the seat next to Nia as she continued talking.

Lileas Graf

“As expected, after the budget reduction, the morale of the employees are at an all time low. Many of them face the risk of losing their jobs now.”

Lileas Graf

“Yet here we are, with mass protests happening in the country, talking about how we have to fire our security force personnel.”

Nia Morgna

“This causes a disastrous bottleneck. How can we deal justice if we can't even find time for these cases?”

Lileas Graf

“As expected, the budget increase has boosted morale of the employees in the law enforcement agencies. In these dire times, my people and Nia's people are especially delighted.”

Lileas Graf

“I think you will be glad to hear that the support for you among the forces is at an all time high, Mr. President.”

Nia Morgna

“Certainly a step in the right direction.”

Lileas Graf

“The current budget has dampened hopes of more funding in the force.”

Lileas Graf

“This comes at an even bigger surprise considering one of the promises that you have made was to focus on our security forces. Yet here we are, exactly where we started at.”

Lileas Graf

“Yet here we are, with mass protests happening in the country. We are standing exactly where we were before.”

Nia Morgna

“Regardless, this means we will have to deal with the growing court backlog. It is manageable but it will be a challenge for sure.”

Player

“Thank you. I am glad you approve.”

Player

“Of course it was the right decision. I made it, after all.”

“Of course it was the right decision. I made it after all.”

Narrator

Nia cast a sidelong look at Lileas.

Player

“Don't worry. I am sure you will manage.”

Lileas Graf

“These sacrifices might've very well damaged the structural integrity of Sordland.”

Lileas Graf

“Tell that to the policemen on the ground when they are overwhelmed by the protestors.”

Nia Morgna

“The ripples are already being felt across the country. I hope this decision is not the beginning of something bad.”

Narrator

Lileas and Nia looked at each other and fell silent.

Player

“Don't worry. I am sure you will manage.”

Player

“You will do as you are told with what you have.”

Narrator

Lileas and Nia looked at each other and fell silent.

Lileas Graf

“Well then. Let's move on to what we are actually here for.”

Lileas Graf

“The Ministry of Interior is a much more significant and important government agency that is in need of the funds. Especially during these times where there are many protests in the country.”

Lileas Graf

“This seems to be an organizational issue, not a funding one. The Interior needs the money more for the police and local governments.”

Player

“What if I decide to balance the budget between Ministry of Interior and Ministry of Justice?”

“What if I decide to balance the budget in between Ministry of Interior and Ministry of Justice?”

Nia Morgna

“Good luck prosecuting criminals or going through local government laws without enough judges, Lileas.”

Nia Morgna

“Of course what would make the most sense in the current situation would be to support the much neglected Ministry of Justice that would improve the legal system in Sordland.”

Player

“I am ready to make a decision.”

Narrator

Lileas and Nia leaned forward.

Player

“The budget will be distributed equally in between the Ministry of Interior and Ministry of Justice.”

Player

“The funds will go to the Ministry of Interior to be used to improve the police and local governments.”

Lileas Graf

“Tell me, Nia. Who brings the criminals before the justices? Let me answer. The police forces connected to Ministry of Interior.”

Lileas Graf

“Due to the budget decrease, we have no choice but to cut funding from a branch.”

Nia Morgna

“You need to make a decision to determine which branch gets the cut.”

Player

“Why should I cut funding from Ministry of Justice?”

Player

“What if I decide to cut funding equally from Ministry of Interior and Ministry of Justice?”

Player

“The funds will be decreased from the Ministry of Justice. It is clearly the less important agency with the current situation.”

Player

“I am ready to make a decision.”

Player

“The funds will be decreased from the Ministry of the Interior. We need to solve the court backlog issue to deal justice.”

Narrator

Lileas and Nia leaned forward.

Player

“I have already made my decision.”

Player

“Budget will be cut equally from the Ministry of Interior and Ministry of Justice.”

Lileas Graf

“Ministry of Interior and our police forces on the ground play a much larger and a more important role during these times where there is a threat to our internal safety.”

Lileas Graf

“Simple. It's because Ministry of Interior can't afford a reduction unless you want the whole country to be overrun with protestors.”

Nia Morgna

“Hah. And tell me Lileas, how are you going to bring the criminals to justice if our judges have to postpone court dates to 6 months, 1 year later.”

Lileas Graf

“That doesn't mean anything. The Ministry of Interior is far more critical in function. Especially now.”

Nia Morgna

“Look at it this way. Ministry of Justice has never been well-funded in Sordland while the Ministry of Interior was always more lucky, already causing this uneven balance in between the two.”

Nia Morgna

“It doesn't even matter who or how many criminals you catch with your forces if justice can't be dealt.”

Lileas Graf

“This is completely absurd and unbefitting for the President of Sordland.”

Nia Morgna

“I knew you would see reason. Thank you.”

Lileas Graf

“I knew that we would be on the same side, Mr. President.”

Lileas Graf

“This is completely absurd and unbefitting for the President of Sordland.”

Lileas Graf

“Before we begin, I'd like to mention your call to boost the police has helped us tremendously in maintaining public safety.”

Narrator

A brief moment of deliberation passed. Nia got up from her seat.

Narrator

A brief moment of deliberation passed. Lileas and Nia got up from their seats.

Narrator

As soon as the door closed, I could hear their muffled voices as they argued.

Narrator

A brief moment of deliberation passed. Lileas got up from her seat.

Nia Morgna

“I must return to the ministry to implement necessary changes.”

Lileas Graf

“I must return to the ministry to implement necessary changes.”

Player

“I don't think so. Our current structure is enough.”

Nia Morgna

“If you accept, this will give our administration the ability to deal with corruption quickly and decisively.”

Player

“I don't think so. Our current structure is enough.”

Nia Morgna

“Excellent. I will start the prep work.”

Narrator

Lileas and Nia got up and left the room.

Player

“I don't think so. Our current structure is enough.”

Nia Morgna

“Regardless, this has been a very productive day. I have to take my leave now as well.”

Nia Morgna

“You are making good decision after good decision today, Mr. President.”

Player

“Very well. Form the Community Police.”

Narrator

They looked at each other before turning to me.

Nia Morgna

“As a sub branch of Ministry of Justice, the ACP would be given full authority by the Presidency to investigate corrupt government officials and citizens.”

Nia Morgna

“While some in the law enforcement agencies look at this negatively we do believe it has the potential to be successful.”

Lileas Graf

“This will come in handy to deal with the protests.”

Lileas Graf

“I must thank you, Mr. President, for the support with the riot gear. The Police Forces definitely needed it.”

Lileas Graf

“At least you have fulfilled our request to fund additional riot control equipment that will allow us to maintain order to some degree.”

Lileas Graf

“What makes things worse is that our request to fund the lacking riot control equipment has been ignored.”

Lileas Graf

“The situation is still not good.”

Lileas Graf

“I am sorry for being late. There was an important matter at the ministry. The security forces of Bergia are arbitrarily not cooperating with my department and created some minor annoyances.”

Lileas Graf

“Luckily they didn't completely botch their tasks, and actually uncovered a large network of priests that are recruiting Bergians for the Bludish Freedom Front.”

Player

"This sounds very significant. Do you want to explain more?"

Player

"Good. Do your best to keep the miscommunication with the Governor's forces to a minimum. We need to take the war against terror seriously."

Lileas Graf

"The issue was a miscommunication about an ongoing investigation inside Bergia. But as I said, it didn't affect the results in a negative way."

Lileas Graf

"The investigation itself, however, revealed some troubling facts. We suspect the existence of a massive network of BFF-aligned priests currently serving in Bergia."

Player

"Thank you for the brief report, Lileas."

Player

"This is worrying news. Keep following the lead. We cannot let these sects divide our society."

Lileas Graf

"If you want my honest opinion, they are a group of dangerous radicals who follow a warped interpretation of Wruhecist Nurity. Most faithful Nurists wouldn't want to have anything to do with them."

Player

"Thank you for the explanation, Lileas."

Player

"Keep following that lead. We cannot let countries like Derdia try and destabilize us with religion."

Lileas Graf

"I suspect the Kingdom of Rizia is involved in this along with Derdia. However, the biggest player is Rumburg and we have clear evidence of their interference. Our focus must be on them."

Lileas Graf

"I thought you might have encountered them during your university days."

Player

"To be honest, I couldn't care less about religion."

Lileas Graf

"Unfortunately, due to my limited authority in the Special Zone of Bergia, I cannot control their operations."
